WEBVTT

00:00.251 --> 00:01.877
<i>Previously on</i> Bosch: Legacy.

00:01.961 --> 00:03.170
People versus Rogers.

00:03.254 --> 00:05.840
- The jury is hopelessly deadlocked.
- Shit.

00:05.840 --> 00:07.967
- You're going to retry him, right?
- We will weigh our options.

00:07.967 --> 00:10.052
How is this even a question?

00:10.136 --> 00:12.221
<i>Rogers hired a hitman
who killed four people,</i>

00:12.221 --> 00:14.682
<i>including a judge,
shot me twice and left me for dead.</i>

00:14.682 --> 00:17.727
- I understand how you feel.
- You have no Goddamn idea how I feel.

00:17.727 --> 00:19.019
What can I do for you, Mr. Vance?

00:19.103 --> 00:21.522
I was hoping you could bring
an old man some peace.

00:21.522 --> 00:25.568
I have no wife, no children
that I know of, no one to leave this to.

00:25.568 --> 00:29.822
There's billions at stake here
and people will do anything to stop you.

00:29.822 --> 00:31.741
Trying to get a hold
of a death certificate.

00:31.741 --> 00:33.826
- Name?
- Vibiana Duarte.

00:33.826 --> 00:35.619
- How did she die?
- Suicide.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.830
I'd like to try and find her child.
Your child.

00:37.830 --> 00:41.208
<i>You heard about Dr. Basu?
Yeah, he was a hero.</i>

00:41.292 --> 00:43.377
He devoted hisself
to the unhoused community.

00:43.461 --> 00:45.963
I gather there's already been an arrest.

00:45.963 --> 00:46.964
Yeah, a homeless man.

00:46.964 --> 00:50.676
Jeffrey, did you tell the detective
that you attacked the doctor?

00:50.760 --> 00:51.761
I wanna go home.

00:51.761 --> 00:53.763
Would you call what you've just seen
a cooked confession?

00:53.763 --> 00:54.722
One hundred percent.

00:54.722 --> 00:58.517
And in your expert opinion, what is
a proper interrogation supposed to be?

00:58.601 --> 01:00.019
A search for the truth.

01:17.036 --> 01:19.413
Cameras, every corner of the house.

01:20.915 --> 01:23.709
Motion detectors, spotlights...

01:23.793 --> 01:25.753
On the bright side, no dogs.

01:25.753 --> 01:27.213
Can you disarm the system?

01:27.213 --> 01:29.673
Man, can Sonny Rollins improvise?

01:29.757 --> 01:31.842
How long to bug the cars?

01:31.926 --> 01:33.219
How many he got?

01:33.219 --> 01:34.762
Two, according to the DMV.

01:34.762 --> 01:36.430
Hmm...

01:36.514 --> 01:37.640
Fifteen, tops.

01:37.640 --> 01:39.350
If they're parked in the driveway.

01:39.350 --> 01:41.477
If they're in the garage?

01:42.520 --> 01:43.521
Thirty.

01:44.730 --> 01:46.273
I'm your first call from jail.

01:47.733 --> 01:48.734
Well, look who's home.

01:50.528 --> 01:52.530
Rogers and his plus one.

01:52.530 --> 01:54.657
Dude, that's the new McLaren GT.

01:54.657 --> 01:57.451
Yo, that shit runs
between 250, 300K.

01:57.535 --> 01:59.453
What's that car do, fly?

01:59.537 --> 02:00.496
Everything but.

02:03.123 --> 02:04.542
And hello, Jasmine.

02:04.542 --> 02:06.544
Uh-oh. Fido.

02:06.544 --> 02:08.128
Plan B?

02:08.212 --> 02:10.881
Tail him wherever he goes.

02:10.965 --> 02:13.425
When the moment's right, bug the cars.

02:13.509 --> 02:16.595
Mercedes's a cinch, but McLaren's
gonna require a little bit of research.

02:16.679 --> 02:17.930
Takes what it takes.

02:19.348 --> 02:20.349
I thought this guy was urgent.

02:21.725 --> 02:22.977
This is just the beginning.

02:27.231 --> 02:28.232
Are you sleeping?

02:30.150 --> 02:30.985
Not great.

02:30.985 --> 02:35.573
I wake up about 3:00 or 4:00 every morning
and can't go back to sleep, so...

02:36.615 --> 02:38.826
The Ambien's not working that well.

02:40.494 --> 02:41.704
The Ativan?

02:41.704 --> 02:45.082
Yeah, it's effective for the most part.

02:45.082 --> 02:46.208
Keeps that, uh...

02:47.877 --> 02:51.505
...you know,
that crazy, panicky feeling at bay.

02:54.049 --> 02:55.092
How's the drinking?

02:56.927 --> 02:58.554
Yeah, I know. Um...

02:58.554 --> 03:01.307
You know, that's...
That's not really my thing.

03:01.307 --> 03:03.517
It's, uh, it's under control.

03:05.227 --> 03:06.103
And work?

03:06.103 --> 03:07.396
Work.

03:09.356 --> 03:12.026
Work keeps my mind off other things.

03:14.278 --> 03:15.112
Like what?

03:17.990 --> 03:18.908
Carl Rogers.

03:22.828 --> 03:24.079
Say more.

03:32.379 --> 03:33.505
What I...

03:33.589 --> 03:35.424
What I think about all the time...

03:39.345 --> 03:40.679
What I really want...

03:44.183 --> 03:49.605
...is to personally hunt him down
and fucking end him.

03:53.692 --> 03:54.526
What's stopping you?

03:59.657 --> 04:00.950
Civilization.

